President Joe Biden has chosen Celeste Drake as the first Director of Made in America at the Office of Management and Budget. In this role, Drake will be responsible for shaping and implementing federal procurement and financial management policies to support the President's goal of promoting American-made products and supporting American workers, including minority entrepreneurs and small businesses. Previously, Drake worked at the Directors Guild of America, where she advocated for the interests of its members. She also served as the Trade and Globalization Policy Specialist for the AFL-CIO, where she played a key role in shaping U.S. trade policy to benefit American workers and the manufacturing sector. Drake has been involved in efforts to reform labor rules, address labor rights violations in various countries, and improve the process for approving trade agreements. She began her career on Capitol Hill and holds a JD, an MPP, and a BA from the University of California, Los Angeles.